Sad news hearing of @viviennewestwood passing. During the early part of my career I often photographed backstage at Vivienne’s shows in Paris. One of my favorite things from her shows was how she brought out the playful nature of the models. #viviennewestwood

Happy new year everyone!!! For 2023 one of my goals is to tell more stories. Faces hold so many layers of us all - every time I film someone I always see something new. To push my storytelling I plan to go beyond seeing more - to listen more - meeting new people and reconnecting with old friends to bring their stories to life. These portraits are from a shoot I did with @radleystudios and @sstieg down in Rio de Janeiro. Two of my best friends were featured in this shoot. ❤️❤️ @juliareisdossantos @bagno_il_faro

“I knew my destiny when I first experienced Yosemite.”

— Ansel Adams

I traveled to Yosemite to study with Alan Ross and learn a bit more about Ansel Adams. Alan is a master printmaker who has been printing Special Edition Ansel Adams prints for over 50 years. 

In Yosemite, we sat in Ansel's darkroom and discussed the art of seeing with intention and how to find all the subtle detail in our black and white imagery.

I think we can all agree that @jaywell_ looks incredible in this image. This series represents my journey in balancing artistry with physicality. It’s a testament to the synchronized efforts of a dedicated team and the physical demands of crafting an image. Each shot stands as evidence of our collective dance of strength, endurance, and vision. From assistants adjusting lights, to Jay and his incredible fitness, it's a collective effort where physicality plays an essential role.

*Teamwork in photography, much like a coordinated workout, is the unsung hero behind every great image. For me, collaboration is more than just working together; it's a symphony of ideas and skills. This series features a collaboration that I have done with designer @hellojohnolson - he's responsible for the incredible graphics here. The background images John selected are from NASA’s James Webb telescope. My original images were shot as part of a project bringing @captureonepro to more members of the LA photo community. @airproductions @milk 

 #photography #creativephotography #creativephotographer #fitness #fitnessmotivation  #collaboration  #trainer
